He's looking for Orca.

111
00:11:59,417 --> 00:12:01,217
Yeah, why?

112
00:12:58,958 --> 00:13:00,792
[Sea is my partner...]

113
00:13:00,792 --> 00:13:02,667
[How could you let Orca take him away?]

114
00:13:02,667 --> 00:13:04,583
[Just because he's famous, does that make him
so special? Does he think he's better than me?]

115
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:08,050
[You're just biased towards Orca.]

116
00:13:15,375 --> 00:13:16,920
[Sea just took a day off.]

117
00:13:16,920 --> 00:13:18,042
[He wanted to talk to Orca
about creative insights.]

118
00:13:18,042 --> 00:13:20,292
[He's still young. Interacting with different
people is really beneficial for him.]

119
00:13:20,292 --> 00:13:23,133
[You don't need to worry so much.]

120
00:13:32,875 --> 00:13:35,750
[He's a Magnet fan.]

121
00:13:35,750 --> 00:13:39,633
[It's only natural for an idol to have fans!]

122
00:13:42,167 --> 00:13:44,300
Why are you here?

123
00:13:52,083 --> 00:13:55,542
Neil, congratulations on your comeback.

124
00:13:55,542 --> 00:13:57,717
I'm happy for you.

125
00:14:05,208 --> 00:14:07,633
What were you two doing?

126
00:14:08,583 --> 00:14:12,383
I was asking Orca's advice on music.

127
00:14:13,583 --> 00:14:15,178
What's there to teach?

128
00:14:15,178 --> 00:14:17,667
He taught me a lot.

129
00:14:17,667 --> 00:14:19,592
Well, you can ask me.

130
00:14:21,229 --> 00:14:25,570
Obviously, Sea has better choices.

131
00:14:28,167 --> 00:14:30,792
You've always liked to steal my thunder.

132
00:14:30,792 --> 00:14:34,300
I'm better than you.

133
00:14:34,300 --> 00:14:37,167
Sea, you'd choose me, right?

134
00:14:37,167 --> 00:14:40,883
Sea, I'm better than him, right?

135
00:14:41,675 --> 00:14:46,793
Sea, will you go on stage to perform with me
at the international music festival?

136
00:14:46,793 --> 00:14:49,120
Orca, shame on you!

137
00:14:49,120 --> 00:14:51,176
What's wrong? Low self-esteem?

138
00:14:51,176 --> 00:14:53,417
I don't understand. Speak Chinese.

139
00:14:53,417 --> 00:14:55,333
I refuse. Learn some Thai!

140
00:14:55,333 --> 00:14:57,967
- Alright, stop the bickering.
- Shut up.

141
00:15:03,958 --> 00:15:07,583
You're just envious of how
Reese is treating me, right?

142
00:15:07,583 --> 00:15:10,217
You'll never get him.

143
